distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the connections of a Pure Storage.
 Monitoring state, throttled-state, version, management address, replication addresses and type.

 The status is mapped to the following Checkmk state:

 - {OK} if state is connected and not throttled unless the service was discovered another state

 - {WARN} if state is connected but throttled and was not discovered throttled

 - {CRIT} if state is disconnected and as not discovered disconnected

 To make this check work you have to configure the related special agent
 {Pure Storage FlashArray}.

item:
 Name of the connection.

discovery:
 One service per connection is created.
